From 7606b734484c0b275edbaf0518a18b0bfaa435dd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dhanavandhana Kannan <dhanavan@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Sep 2025 15:01:30 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:wifi: ath12k: Fix restrict link agnostic
 bit for WNM frames to MLO mode

Set the ATH12K_SKB_MGMT_LINK_AGNOSTIC bit for BSS Transition
Management (BTM) Request and Response frames only when
operating in Multi-Link Operation (MLO) mode.

This change ensures that the bit is set only when multiple links
are active and station is multi link in ath12k_mac_get_tx_link()
and not in ath12k_mac_mgmt_action_frame_fill_elem(),aligning with
expected MLO behavior and avoiding misclassification in legacy
(non-MLO) cases.

Patch-dependency: 0523-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-wifi-ath12k-set-link-
agnostic-for-.patch

Patch-work: None

Fixes: Ic48739cf33e7 (UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:wifi: ath12k: set
link-agnostic for BSS transition frames)

Signed-off-by: Dhanavandhana Kannan <dhanavan@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
index df4e269..90a977d 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
@@ -14509,8 +14509,11 @@ check_rm_action_frame:
 			 * BTM request and response as per
 			 * IEEE Std 802.11be Draft 7.0,
 			 * section 35.3.14
+			 *
+			 * Intentionally leaving the switch case empty
+			 * to avoid resetting the link agnostic bit in
+			 * default case.
 			 */
-			skb_cb->flags |= ATH12K_SKB_MGMT_LINK_AGNOSTIC;
 			break;
 		default:
 			skb_cb->flags &= ~ATH12K_SKB_MGMT_LINK_AGNOSTIC;
-- 
